1) Simple
	- easy to understand
	- contains the same syntax as C, and C++,
	- pointers has been completely removed from Java
2) Object Oriented
3) Robust
	-  capable of handling unexpected termination of a program
4) Platform Independent
	- allows programmers to write their program on any machine with any configuration
	and to execute it on any other machine having different configurations
5) Portable

6) Secure
7) Interpreted
8) Multi-Threaded